<title>USA: Class certified in consumer case against H.I.P..</title>
<headline>Class certified in consumer case against H.I.P..</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-01-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Supreme Court of the State of New York has granted class certification in a consumer fraud case against  H.I.P. of Greater New York, according to Wolf Popper LLP.</p>
<p>The firm, which represents the case's plantiffs, said the case alleges the H.I.P. wrongfully refused to provide to certain of its subscribers reimbursement for the services of anesthesiologists.</p>
<p>The class, as certified, includes all H.I.P. subscribers who, since June 7, 1993, were denied such coverage based on an exclusion in H.I.P.'s policies for &quot;anesthesia.&quot;</p>
<p>((-- New York Newsdesk 212-859-1610.))</p>
